VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8080

# ── map-service (optional overrides) ────────────────────────────────────────
# By default the frontend talks to the map-service SAME-ORIGIN: REST via `/api/*`
# and realtime via `/ws/map`, proxied to the map-service by the Vite dev server
# (see src/lib/devProxy.ts) and by nginx in prod. Override these only if the map
# paths are mounted under a different prefix / host.
#   VITE_MAP_API_BASE_URL=/api
#   VITE_MAP_WS_URL=ws://localhost:8081/ws/map

# ── LOCAL-ONLY dev identity shim (NEVER set in production) ───────────────────
# Production NEVER forges identity headers — the map-service derives the user from
# the validated session (Bearer/cookie via a trusted gateway). For LOCAL dev against
# a bare map-service (its `local` profile reads `X-User-Id` directly, with no gateway
# in front), opt in explicitly to send X-User-Id/X-Username from the logged-in user.
# This is compiled out of any production build (`import.meta.env.DEV` is false there).
#   VITE_MAP_DEV_IDENTITY=true
#   VITE_MESSENGER_DEV_IDENTITY=true
